OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Edward H. Bastian  CEO & Director, Delta Air Lines, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships59$12,557,231As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Edward H. Bastian, also known as Ed, has been the Chief Executive Officer of Delta Air Lines, Inc. since May 2, 2016. Mr. Bastian served as President of Delta Air Lines, Inc. from September 01, 2007 to May 2, 2016. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of NWA, Inc. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Northwest Airlines, LLC from October 2008 to December 2009 and also served as its Chief Operating Officer. He served as the President ... and Chief Executive Officer at Northwest Airlines, Inc. He served as Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President of Delta Air Lines Inc. from July 20, 2005 to September 2007 and also served as its Principal Accounting Officer. Mr. Bastian rejoined Delta and is a six-year Delta veteran. He served as Senior Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of Acuity Brands, Inc. from June 1, 2005 to July 2005. He has over twenty-five years of financial experience. He joined Delta in October 1998 as Vice President of Finance and was promoted to Senior Vice President of Finance and Controller of Delta Air Lines Inc. in February 2000. His responsibilities at Delta included internal and external financial reporting, financial planning and analysis and Sarbanes-Oxley implementation and compliance. He spearheaded the implementation of SAP financial systems at Delta, including process and organization redesign and was instrumental in its cost reduction efforts following the events of September 11, 2001. Mr. Bastian served as Vice President of Finance and Controller of Frito-Lay International and as a Partner with Price Waterhouse in its audit practice for 13 years in entertainment, advertising and manufacturing areas. He was also the Strategic Planning Partner for Price Waterhouse's New York Region. He worked with Pepsico where he served as Vice President of business process re-engineering for Frito Lay. He has been an Independent Director of Grupo Aeromexico S.A.B. de C.V. since 2012. He has been a Director of Delta Air Lines, Inc. since February 5, 2010. He served as a Director of GOL Linhas Aéreas Inteligentes S.A. from 2012 to May 5, 2016. He served as a Director of Northwest Airlines, LLC. Mr. Bastian is a graduate of St. Bonaventure University with a BBA in 1979 and is also a Certified Public Accountant.Read Full Background




